window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Start the number one best-selling ARISEN series - which fans are calling</i> “<b>the best zombie apocalypse series ever written</b>,” “<b>an edge of your seat thrill ride - the best zombie thriller since WWZ</b>,” and “<b>an adrenaline-laced rush</b>”<i> - right from the beginning of the end, with the first two books together...</i> </p> <p><b>Volume 1 - </b><b><i>The Collapse</i></b> </p> <p><i>Two teams of spec-ops Marines left to die in the fall of North America</i> </p> <p><i>One carrier strike group, humanity's last best hope for survival</i> </p> <p><i>And 7 billion ravening dead guys, devouring an overrun planet</i> </p> <p>Climb aboard the USS <i>John F. Kennedy</i>, the most complex and deadly warship ever built by man, along with its pipe-hitting Marine Raider guardians, to experience two years of horrors and glories of the Zulu Alpha across the world's fallen ports and coasts. Now, after the epic 14-book ARISEN main series, the story before the story can finally be told… </p> <p><b>Volume 2 - </b><b><i>Tribes</i></b> </p> <p>Doc Yaz, Gunny Blane, and the rest of the Raiders are safely back on the <i>Kennedy</i> after surviving the horrific collapse of North America. But they are instantly thrust back onto shore, and into the worst of the ZA, to secure the critical supplies the strike group needs to survive even another day - and the weapons and ammo the Marines need to keep fighting for everyone else. Hold your breath as these shore missions go from simple, to stupid, to suicidal, all with breathtaking speed and violence. Keep the tribe alive. </p> <p><b><i>ARISEN</i></b> </p> <p><b>Hope Never Dies.</b> </p>"; 
